textBody:
Alexander I may refer to:

* Alexander I of Macedon, king of Macedon 495–450 BC
* Alexander I of Epirus (370 BC–331 BC), King of Epirus about 342 BC
* Pope Alexander I (died 115), Pope from 106 to 115
* Pope Alexander I of Alexandria (died 320s), Patriarch of Alexandria about 320
* Alexander I of Scotland (c. 1078–1124), King of Scotland
* Alexander I of Georgia (1386–?), King of Georgia
* Alexandru cel Bun, (?–1432) Alexander I of Moldavia, prince
* Alexander I of Kakheti (1445–1511), King of Kakheti
* Alexander I Jagiellon (1461–1506), King of Poland
* Alexander I of Russia (1777–1825), Emperor of Russia
* Alexander of Bulgaria (1857–1893), Prince of Bulgaria
* Alexander I of Serbia (1876–1903), King of Serbia
* Alexander I of Yugoslavia (1888–1934), King of Yugoslavia
* Alexander of Greece (1893–1920), King of Greece
